  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Also he took away out of all the cities of Judah the high places and the images,.... Perhaps the high places in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 14:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " design only the high places and altars in Jerusalem, and near it; these in all the rest of the cities of the land; the \"images were\", as the word signifies, \"sun images\", either made in the form of the sun, or dedicated to it, or temples for it; See Gill on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 26:30",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the kingdom was quiet before him; he had no foreign enemy to molest him, and so took that opportunity to reform divine worship, and in that he met with no opposition from his people. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and the kingdom was quiet before him; he had no foreign enemy to molest him, and so took that opportunity to reform divine worship, and in that he met with no opposition from his people. ",
